        <h1>ONLINE HELP</h1>
        <h3><ol><b>Transport Officer</b></ol></h3>
        <p>
            <b>instructions</b><br>
            1. Login <br>
            The user Logs in as admin by inputing their admin staff Id's and password <br>
            The transport officer is directed to the dashboard below <br>
            <img src="transportOfficer.PNG" style="width : 50% ; height : 20% ; margin-left: 5px ;" ><br>
            <br>
            <br>
            <br>
            <br>
            
            2. The <b>REGISTER STAFF</b> tab enables the transport officer to register a new staff member<br>
            while specifying their roles.<br>
            <br>
            3. The <b>REGISTER VEHICLE</b> tab enables the transport officer to register a new vehicle<br>
            and add it to the system.<br>
            <br>
            4. The <b>VIEW TRIPS</b> tab enables the transport officer to view pending academic  trips and approve them<br> and assigning driver and vehicle.They can also view pending official trips<br>
            and either approve or cancel them.Approval requires them to specify a vehicle and driver While<br>canceling requires them to provide a reason for cancellation.<br>They can also view a list of approved and cancelled trips.<br>
            <br>
            5. The <b>VIEW REPORTS</b> tab enables the transport officer to view driver and mechanic reports based on their <br>
            specifications.<br>
            <br>
            6. The <b>DELETE STAFF</b> tab enables the transport officer to remove a staff member from the system by giving<br>
            the staff id of the member.<br>
            <br>
            7. The <b>DELETE VEHICLE</b> tab enables the transport officer to remove a vehicle from the system by giving<br>
            the plate number of the vehicle.<br>
            <br>
            8. The <b>LOGOUT </b> tab logs the user out of the system<br>
            <br>
            <br>
        </p>
